      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes, CapCut's Standard plan is free and includes auto captions, templates, basic effects, and exporting capabilities. The Pro plan adds watermark-free exports, advanced AI tools, expanded cloud storage, and brand kit features for a modest monthly fee. Most solo creators find the free plan sufficient for producing high-quality content.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can CapCut replace professional editing software like Premiere Pro?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For short-form content, social media videos, and standard YouTube production, CapCut absolutely holds its own. It handles 90% of common editing tasks faster than traditional NLEs thanks to its AI features and templates. For complex multi-cam broadcasts, color grading pipelines, or advanced compositing, you'll still want a professional tool. But CapCut is increasingly becoming the first choice for creators who value speed and efficiency.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Does CapCut work on both mobile and desktop?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes, CapCut is available on iOS, Android, Windows, and Mac. Projects can sync across devices via the cloud, so you can start editing on your phone and finish on your desktop. The desktop version offers a fuller timeline experience with more precise controls, while the mobile app is optimized for quick edits and social media publishing.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How accurate are CapCut's AI auto captions?",
